This repository contains tools to deploy test/dev two-node Openshift clusters ([Two Node with Arbiter](deploy/tna-ipi-baremetalds-virt/) and Two Node with Fencing configurations) 

Both of them need expected a valid RHEL hypervisor, which will then provision all necessary VMs to create and set up the two-node cluster. 
If you don't have one available, the [dev-env-aws-hypervisor](deploy/dev-env-aws-hypervisor/) folder provides instructions and tools to automatically create this base host in AWS.

Once the hypervisor is setup, you can use the [TNA](deploy/tna-ipi-baremetalds-virt/) and TNF folders to create those specific clusters within that newly provisioned host, or on your own one. 

More information on two-node configurations can be found in the [docs](docs) folder